events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Detroit Pistons
New Orleans Pelicans at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Zion Williamson scored 31 points while dominating inside, and the New Orleans Pelicans ended a three-game skid with a 144-113 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williamson strong inside, Pelicans trounce Grizzlies 144-113

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet scored 33 points, Pascal Siakam added 23 and the Toronto Raptors withstood the loss of Kyle Lowry to beat the slumping Milwaukee Bucks 124-113 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors beat Bucks 124-113 despite losing Lowry to injury

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 30 points, 13 rebounds and seven assists and Dennis Schröder scored 24 points, helping the Los Angeles Lakers pull away from the Minnesota Timberwolves for a 112-104 victory on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: James, Lakers, minus Davis, fend off Timberwolves 112-104

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard scored 12 of his 31 points in the final 4:11 to help the Portland Trail Blazers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 115-104 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard scores 31 as Trail Blazers top Thunder 115-104

headlines.description: — James Harden scored 38 points, Joe Harris added 22 and the Brooklyn Nets overcame a 24-point deficit to stun the Phoenix Suns 128-124 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harden scores 38, Nets rally from 24 down, stun Suns 128-124
